text:
Branding professional chiming in to say absolutely yes. 

Before even mentioning the name I have to address the fact that the branding should all be the Arch Gate logo as well with this change üôè . The Purple is and always has been one of the best organic brand signifiers (The Purple App!) and the arch is really strong.

I'd say (personal opinion) the names were always too similar and would lead to confusion. At this point a consolidation seems to work best and as new clients emerge, with their own branding, this remains Farcaster, the OG client. I like @derek's suggestion of Farcaster (client) Farcaster API (protocol). 

Also while Warpcast is a cool product name, it feels off for what the product is. Warp implies something that just never seemed to fit or flow with the product in usage or branding, Iikely why so many people end up referring to it as Farcaster or FC. Cast btw, as has been discussed elsewhere, is EXCELLENT branding and should be highlighted at every turn.

LAUNCH

Universal Bridge ‚ú®

Let users pay with whatever they have without leaving your app.

Crypto payments are broken. L2s have helped Ethereum scale, but caused fragmented liquidity & unnecessary complexity.

Most users churn when they have to bridge or swap funds outside of your app.

Universal Bridge ensures your users never get stuck on the 'wrong' chain.

It finds the best route for every transaction ‚Äî swapping, on-ramping, or bridging, and abstracts the process for the user.
